cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 175 miles SW of Ft. Myers, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving north-northeast, expected to skirt the southwest Florida coast, make landfall on the northern Florida Gulf Coast, then cross north-central Florida and exit into the western Atlantic
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near the Nature Coast (Cedar Key–Levy County area, FL)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Hurricane Watch: Anna Maria Island to Yankeetown, FL.  Tropical Storm Watch: north of Suwannee River to Aucilla River, FL.
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning: Dry Tortugas and Bonita Beach to Suwannee River, FL.
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Entire west coast of Florida from Bonita Beach northward to the Big Bend, then across north-central FL and into the northeast FL/GA Atlantic coast.
weather_observation.wind: Chance of tropical-storm-force gusts Thursday into early Friday with peak probabilities about 9% (sustained 34-kt).  50-kt winds are unlikely (3% cumulative).
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected on the Atlantic side of northeast Florida; surge watches limited to Gulf coast.
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands from Eta could drop 2–4 inches Thursday; localized totals to 4 inches may cause brief ponding and runoff issues.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous rip currents and elevated surf along northeast Florida beaches Thursday–Friday.
